UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1935
1 request a summary, to be prepared in accordance with subsection (3) of this
2 section, for any part of the Medicaid state plan; and
3 (b) The department shall, within five (5) calendar days after the effective date
4 of this Act, provide the Legislative Research Commission with a copy of the
5 current, in effect Medicaid and KCHIP state plans for referral to the
6 Interim Joint Committee on Health Services and the Medicaid Oversight
7 and Advisory Board.
8 Section 2. Whereas recently enacted federal changes to the Medicaid program
9 and significant increases in the Commonwealth's Medicaid budget over the last decade
10 create an urgent need to bolster legislative oversight of the Medicaid program, take
11 immediate steps to comply with new federal requirements, and ensure that Medicaid
12 expenditures support the healthcare needs of only those individuals the program is
13 intended to serve, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its
14 passage and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
